A dangerous suspect has escaped police custody in Norkem Park in Ekurhuleni, Gauteng, reports the Tembisan.
“Michael Vundla (39) has the intention to cause serious bodily harm,” Capt Lesibana Molokomme, spokesperson for the Norkem Park SAPS told Express on Friday.
According to Molokomme, Vundla was arrested and detained for assault on April 13, after which he escaped from custody.
“The suspect is from Umthambeka section in Tembisa. He is suspected to be around the Tembisa area,” Molokomme added.
Anyone with information on his whereabouts can contact Norkem Park D/Const Miyalane Mashautane on 011 391 1814/5, call the emergency number 08600 10111 or the closest police station.